Package: rikus-mintshot
Version: 7.2
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Gilbert Rikus <gilbert@rikus.info>
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Replaces: linux-mint-snapshot
Provides: linux-mint-snapshot
Conflicts: linux-mint-snapshot
Depends: python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, polkitd, pkexec, calamares, live-boot, live-config-systemd, live-boot-initramfs-tools, xorriso, isolinux, syslinux-common, squashfs-tools, grub-efi-amd64-bin, grub-pc-bin, shim-signed, grub-efi-amd64-signed, mtools, dosfstools, gdisk, fdisk, parted, e2fsprogs, rsync, procps, x11-xserver-utils, os-prober, efibootmgr, wget, openssh-client
Recommends: mintstick
Homepage: https://github.com/Zahnschmerz/rikus-mintshot
Description: One-click bootable clone of your running Linux Mint system
 Rikus Mintshot builds a bootable live ISO of your running Linux Mint
 installation with one click. Choose what goes in: bare system only,
 system plus your settings (lean but ready to use), or a full 1:1 clone
 including all your data. A system-cloning tool that Linux Mint has no
 built-in equivalent for.
 .
 It uses the refractasnapshot engine and a custom-configured Calamares
 installer for a full takeover on install (account, settings and logins
 come straight from the clone). Boots with Secure Boot on or off (signed
 shim + GRUB chain). GUI in German or English, chosen automatically.
 Free and open source (GPL-3.0).
 .
 This package installs the application and its data files and pulls in
 the required build/live/install tooling. The off-repository
 refractasnapshot-base engine is fetched automatically on first run.
